  <data key="d1">"CERCLA is a federal law enacted in 1980 that authorized the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to create a list of polluted locations requiring long-term response for environmental remediation."&lt;SEP&gt;"CERCLA is a federal law enacted in 1980 that authorized the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to create a list of polluted locations requiring long-term response for environmental remediation."&lt;&lt;SEP&gt;"CERCLA is a federal law enacted in 1980 that authorizes the EPA to create the National Priorities List (NPL) and take action to clean up hazardous material contaminations."&lt;SEP&gt;"CERCLA is a federal law enacted in 1980 that authorizes the United States Environmental Protection Agency to clean up hazardous waste sites."&lt;SEP&gt;"CERCLA is a federal law that authorized the creation of a list of polluted locations requiring long-term response for cleanup."&lt;SEP&gt;"Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act (CERCLA&lt;SEP&gt;"Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act (CERCLA) is an environmental law that designates Superfund sites."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83dc7cbdd7b7292338f3c15ee07a3a52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8260399c9bfacaab98ca9b225ec9585&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d66f5a4049fbfee0e93adcd014ceb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e099c9aaaf8a8993a977e55494066d38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fe7530c2ba6261298c312542f90c06a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 11}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNITED STATES ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY (EPA)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"EPA is the agency responsible for creating and managing the National Priorities List of Superfund sites."&lt;SEP&gt;"The EPA is responsible for creating the National Priorities List (NPL) for Superfund sites and guiding the cleanup process."&lt;SEP&gt;"The EPA is responsible for creating the National Priorities List (NPL) for Superfund sites and guiding the cleanup process."&lt;&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) is authorized to create a list of polluted locations requiring a long-term response to clean up hazardous material contaminations, known as Superfund sites, and to place these sites on the National Priorities List (NPL)."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States Environmental Protection Agency is a federal agency responsible for protecting human health and the environment."&lt;SEP&gt;"United States Environmental Protection Agency is a federal agency responsible for protecting human health and the environment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1d66f5a4049fbfee0e93adcd014ceb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e099c9aaaf8a8993a977e55494066d38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc344349affa2888cf0ab0e3db5f4cf6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83dc7cbdd7b7292338f3c15ee07a3a52</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 11}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATIONAL PRIORITIES LIST (NPL)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"NPL is the list maintained by EPA to guide the determination of which sites warrant further investigation for environmental remediation."&lt;SEP&gt;"National Priorities List is a list maintained by the EPA that identifies the most serious uncontrolled or abandoned hazardous waste sites in the United States."&lt;SEP&gt;"The NPL is a list of polluted locations that require further investigation and cleanup under the CERCLA law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The NPL is a list of polluted locations that require further investigation and cleanup under the CERCLA law."&lt;&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Priorities List (NPL) guides the EPA in determining which sites warrant further investigation for environmental remediation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Priorities List (NPL) is a list used by the EPA to guide the selection of sites for further investigation and environmental remediation based on the severity of contamination."&lt;SEP&gt;"The National Priorities List is a list maintained by the EPA that identifies the most serious uncontrolled or abandoned hazardous waste sites in the United States."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-83dc7cbdd7b7292338f3c15ee07a3a52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d66f5a4049fbfee0e93adcd014ceb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e099c9aaaf8a8993a977e55494066d38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fe7530c2ba6261298c312542f90c06a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc344349affa2888cf0ab0e3db5f4cf6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 11}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}]</data>
</node>
