<node id="&quot;SUPERFUND SITES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Superfund sites are locations designated under CERCLA for cleanup of hazardous material contaminations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superfund sites are locations designated under the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act (CERCLA) for cleaning up hazardous material contaminations. They are placed on the National Priorities List (NPL) to guide the EPA in determining which sites warrant further investigation for environmental remediation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superfund sites are locations designated under the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act (CERCLA) for cleanup of hazardous material contaminations, guided by the National Priorities List (NPL). There are 11 such sites in Vermont as of November 29, 2010."&lt;SEP&gt;"Superfund sites are locations requiring a long-term response to clean up hazardous material contaminations, as determined by the EPA and placed on the National Priorities List (NPL)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1d66f5a4049fbfee0e93adcd014ceb71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fe7530c2ba6261298c312542f90c06a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc344349affa2888cf0ab0e3db5f4cf6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf4700a1a1ea9062f552bc2637f2f658</data>
